{{Quote|Works for me. Files say the Mitth family runs things on Copero. Is that right?''"<br />"''Their shipbuilding business has hit some hard times. House Inrokini bailed them out with a huge investment, so they're the real power these days. Not that Mitth advertises the fact, of course.''"<br />"''Sounds like I need to make some friends from Inrokini, then.|[[Pova]] and [[Theron Shan]]|<ref name="Chasing Copero">{{TORweb|url=info/news/news-article/20171116|text="Chasing Copero"|int=Chasing Copero}}</ref>}}
The '''Inrokini family''', also known as '''House Inrokini''', was a [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] [[Ruling Families/Legends|Ruling Family]] responsible for industry, science, communication,<ref name="The Chiss" /> and non-military<ref name="UAA">''[[Ultimate Alien Anthology]]''</ref> or civilian technology.<ref name="NEGtAS">''[[The New Essential Guide to Alien Species]]''</ref> The [[Chiss family/Legends|family]]'s [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] was the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Csaus/Legends|Csaus]], a hub of science and communications in the Ascendancy.<ref name="The Essential Atlas" /> An Inrokini family banner was adorned by a [[Unidentified Chiss crest|crest]].<ref name="A Traitor Among the Chiss" />

Sometime before the [[Order of Zildrog campaign]] [[Syndic/Legends|Syndic]] [[Zenta]] adopted a [[Force-sensitive/Legends|force sensitive]] [[Valss]] to the Inrokini family. The two later allied themselves with [[Theron Shan]] when he came to [[Copero/Legends|Copero]] seeking a [[Holomap/Legends|Holomap]] to the [[Superweapon/Legends|superweapon]] of the [[Sith Emperor]] [[Tenebrae|Vitiate]]. For that they were considered traitors by [[Aristocra/Legends|Aristocra]] [[Saganu]].

In [[28 ABY/Legends|28 ABY]],<ref name="FHII Date">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates the events of ''[[The New Jedi Order: Force Heretic II: Refugee]]'' to [[28 ABY/Legends|28 ABY]].</ref> a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] delegation led by [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] visited the planet [[Csilla/Legends|Csilla]] in their [[Hunt for Zonama Sekot|search]] for the [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Zonama Sekot/Legends|Zonama Sekot]]. There, a representative of the Inrokini family attended a meeting of the [[Council of Families]] with the delegation&mdash;alongside other representatives of the Four Families&mdash;which took place in the [[City/Legends|city]] of [[Ac'siel]] on the [[Capital/Legends|capital]] planet.<ref name="FHII">''[[The New Jedi Order: Force Heretic II: Refugee]]''</ref>

{{Chiss-stub}}

